.TH "drm_dp_dpcd_read_phy_link_status" 9 "drm_dp_dpcd_read_phy_link_status" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dp_dpcd_read_phy_link_status \- get the link status information for a DP PHY
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_dp_dpcd_read_phy_link_status
.BI "(struct drm_dp_aux *aux "  ","
.BI "enum drm_dp_phy dp_phy "  ","
.BI "u8 link_status[DP_LINK_STATUS_SIZE] "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "aux" 12
DisplayPort AUX channel
.IP "dp_phy" 12
the DP PHY to get the link status for
.IP "link_status" 12
buffer to return the status in
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Fetch the AUX DPCD registers for the DPRX or an LTTPR PHY link status. The
layout of the returned \fIlink_status\fP matches the DPCD register layout of the
DPRX PHY link status.

Returns 0 if the information was read successfully or a negative error code
on failure.
